<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: Race vs. Race</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Stupid">Stupid</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 3:02 p.m. 7/5/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: Race vs. Race<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=2029" TARGET=_self>Race vs. Race</A> (Ice)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> Is this a bad thing or not?

<P>Personally, I detest this. I feel that Verant has provided an excellent role playing environment with a set "role" for evey player. In my opinion, the racial/alignment guidlines were set up for a reason and they should be adhered to. Yes, Dark Elves have no Druids or Bards. That's a limitation. But on the other hand, Dark Elves have Ultravision - almost perfect night vision - no other race has this. That's an advantage. It all works out.
<P>My feeling is that each race was designed to be more-or-less balanced in the "big picture". Between Dark Elves, Trolls and Ogres, (so-called) "evil" races have access to every possible skill and spell in the game. Why would you need (or even WANT) to group with (so-called) "good" races and classes?
<P>I guess, deep down, I'm a role player. But I'm the minority. Most people, it seems, are unwilling (or unable) to accept the limitations that the game implies. But while I dislike it, I also know that there is very little that I can do to change it.
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
